        "single-column_text": "<h2>Wool Innovation</h2><p></p><p>Gisborne Airport and Ngai Tāwhiri recently hosted a native planting day at the entrance of the airport. The community initiative focused on promoting environmental sustainability and biodiversity within the premises.<br/><br/>Gisborne Airport Manager Murray Bell said, \"One way of achieving this was by using more eco-friendly alternatives such as wool weed matting.\"<br/><br/>Wool.Life NZ sources the wool from local Tairāwhiti farms and manufactures it into conventional weed matting, improving biodegradability and enhancing water retention.</p>",
